In our documentation on [Greenhopper JIRA Documentation|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/GreenHopper+JIRA+Configuration#GreenHopperJIRAConfiguration-Customfields], we state for the  *type* columns on Epic custom fields (Epic Colour, Epic Name, Epic Link and Epic Status):

{quote}
... and is available to all issue types.
{quote}

This is incorrect. The only of the above custom fields that is available to all issue types is the "Epic Link", all the other Epic custom fields are available only for the Epic issue type.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-9441].
  {panel}

Seen on JAC in 6.2.4 v J6.1 and locally v J5.2
--

*Steps to reproduce:*
# Go to _Board Configuration > Filter_;
# Click to edit the Saved Filter;
# Remove current text/name and observe the error:

