h3. According to customer:
{quote}
Assume that the same team has to work on features as well as bugs. I want to get bugs reported under an Epic called as Bugs for a team that works on project features. On one dashboard and under epic, I would like to see items from different projects configured in Jira/GH. In any company there can be multiple projects created in Jira but there will be dependencies. There can be overlap of engineers. How do you do all these in GH without a feature that helps me to put under an epic and use other features you provide?
{quote}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-9364].
  {panel}

As of now, the _Commits_ tab of the Issue Detail pane displays only the username of the author and links to the repository. It should display the same details that are included in the Issue View screen in JIRA.

h3. Steps to reproduce:
# Create a new user _'bulkmover'_;
# Add it on the 'jira-users' group;
# Browse to _Administration -> Global Permissions_ and remove the _'jira-user'_ group on the _'Bulk Change'_ permission;
# Log with the _'bulkmover'_ user, create a new board and a test sprint; Add some issues on it.
# Now, click on _'Agile'_ and select the new board you'd just created;
# On the board, right-click on an issue -> _'Bulk Change'_;
!bulkmovegh.png!

h3. Current behaviour:
# JIRA will bulk move the issue even though the user has no global permission for doing so:
!bulkmoveop.png!
# If this same user have gone through the issue navigator, the _'Bulk Move'_ option won't be available for him; The global permission is working properly on JIRA;
# If the user try to hit http://baseurl/secure/BulkChooseOperation!default.jspa, he will got a timeout error; Probably because no issues has been selected, but the permission does not seem to be respected here as well;
# The same happens if you create a _'Classic Board'_. A user can bulk change issues without permission:
!ghclassicbulkmove.png!

h3. Expected Behaviour
# GreenHopper shall respect the global permission and wouldn't show the 'Bulk Move'/'Bulk Operations' when a user hasn't such rights in both -- classic and new boards.
